# Add Ring Badge to RelatedPosts Avatar

## Context
The RelatedPosts card already shows a `VerifiedBadge` icon next to the author name, but doesn't show the glowing ring around the avatar that exists elsewhere in the app (PostCards, UserSearchResults, Notifications, etc.). The `post.user_badge` field is already returned by the backend query.

## Changes

### 1. `client/src/components/Discovery/RelatedPosts.jsx` (lines 66-75)
Wrap the avatar `<img>` / placeholder `<div>` in a container `<div>` with the conditional ring class:

```jsx
<div className={`rp-card-avatar-container ${post.user_badge === 'legend' ? 'rp-avatar-ring-legend' : post.user_badge === 'og' ? 'rp-avatar-ring-og' : ''}`}>
    {post.user_image_url ? (
        <img src={post.user_image_url} alt="" className="rp-card-avatar" />
    ) : (
        <div className="rp-card-avatar rp-card-avatar-placeholder" />
    )}
</div>
```

### 2. `client/src/components/Discovery/RelatedPosts.css`
Add ring styles after `.rp-card-avatar-placeholder` (after line 147), following the existing small-avatar ring pattern (22px avatar, 2px border, subtle glow):

- `.rp-card-avatar-container` — base wrapper (border-radius: 50%, flex-shrink: 0)
- `.rp-avatar-ring-legend` — gold ring (`#FFD700`, glow, pulse animation)
- `.rp-avatar-ring-og` — purple ring (`#9B59FF`, glow, pulse animation)
- Keyframes: `rp-glow-legend` and `rp-glow-og`

## Verification
- View a post whose author has `badge = 'legend'` or `'og'` — avatar should show glowing ring
- Authors without a badge should render identically to current behavior
